(2424, 'options_my_courses_content', '<aside class="text-primary-dark"></aside><aside class="text-primary-dark">Workshop Etiquette-In order for our courses to maintain a professional atmosphere and efficient order, we ask all attendees to adhere to our simple golden rules.</aside><aside class="text-primary-dark">Please:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>As a courtesy to organisers and presenters, always register for a course before attending.</li>\r\n	<li>Arrive on time for registration to avoid being late for the session. If you do arrive late, please find your place quickly and quietly.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep unnecessary noise and conversation, both immediately outside and inside venue rooms, to a minimum.</li>\r\n	<li>Be respectful of both the presenters and your peers and do not talk during the session.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure your mobile phone is off or on silent. If you need to take a call, please quietly step outside the session.</li>\r\n	<li>Become involved in discussions, but please show courtesy to the presenter of stopping when called upon.</li>\r\n	<li>Always wear appropriate and non-offensive clothing. When offered, wear your name tag so you can be readily identified as an official registrant, and for ease of communication.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</aside>', 'no'),
