(518, 18, '2015-11-07 03:55:05', '2015-11-07 03:55:05', '<strong>There are growing requests from teachers for support on how to effectively engage students who are reluctant to learn at school especially in the vital area of Literacy. There is also a need to update teachers’ professional knowledge in using ICT as a powerful tool that can make a greater difference in learning. We are pleased to provide a workshop using ICT to improve student engagement for reluctant learners within the Early and Middle Years focusing on Literacy.</strong>\n\nSuitability<em>:</em>\n\nThis workshop is suitable for Educators (Primary, Secondary &amp; Special Needs), Support staff and pre-service teachers.\n\n<em><u>Workshop Overview:</u></em>\n\nThis full day eLearning Literacy workshop for classroom teachers, address the key issues in student disengagement that prevent students from reaching their full potential. Teachers will participate in innovative and practical hands-on literacy activities (especially using ICT) that motivate reluctant learners, improve student outcomes and can be immediately applied in the Early Years and Middle Years classrooms.\n\n<em>This full day workshop will allow classroom teachers to successfully:</em>\n<ul>\n	<li>Identify key issues that disengage students in Literacy;</li>\n	<li>Understand how to engage students using effective eLearning strategies &amp; tools;</li>\n	<li>Experience the most relevant and motivating use of ICT to achieve student outcomes in Literacy at different learning stages;</li>\n	<li>Apply all e5 Principles using ICT to ensure learning progress;</li>\n	<li>Provide incidental authentic assessment opportunities that guide achievable learning outcomes;</li>\n	<li>Be empowered to make a positive difference</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><u>Here is some feedback we have had from teachers about this Workshop:</u></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>“A fun and engaging way to hook teachers into becoming extraordinary teachers – not ordinary teachers!”</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>“This workshop stops you from thinking that reluctant learners are lazy, or can’t do things, but shows you that these learners  are just not ready to learn, and demonstrates various ways to help engage them and get them ready in life.”</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>“This is a highly professional, relevant, informative and ‘hands on’ P.D. The best P.D I have been to!”</em></p>', 'Engaging Reluctant Literacy Learners- Werribee', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'engaging-reluctant-literacy-learners-werribee-2', '', '', '2015-11-07 03:55:05', '2015-11-07 03:55:05', '', 0, 'http://teachmepd.com.au/', 0, 'tribe_events', '', 0),
(520, 18, '2015-11-07 03:55:05', '2015-11-07 03:55:05', '<strong>Blogging is transforming the way we learn, collaborate and reflect. It offers authentic assessment opportunities, improves literacy skills and can be used by educators for many purposes including classroom digital portfolios, professional portfolios and as a professional learning tool.  Find out just how easy it is to setup your own blog for yourself and for your students.</strong>\n\n<em><u>Suitability:</u></em>\n\nThis workshop is suitable for Educators (Primary, Secondary &amp; Special Needs), Support staff and pre-service teachers.\n\n<em><u>Workshop Overview:</u></em>\n\nTeachers will experience practical hands on activities, professional conversations, blogging tools and additional support resources throughout the entire day.\n\n<em>This hands-on eLearning workshop will allow classroom teachers to successfully:</em>\n<ul>\n	<li>Understand what Blogs are, including different types and uses;</li>\n	<li>Create a simple Word Press Blog via edublogs (private school teachers) or Global 2 (public school teachers);</li>\n	<li>Explore how blogs improve student literacy skills and engagement;</li>\n	<li>Experience how blogs can be used as powerful authentic assessment tools;</li>\n	<li>Access strategies and activities to use blogs effectively in the classroom based on student needs and stages of learning;</li>\n	<li>Access outstanding blogs that can be used with students in the classroom to support different areas of the curriculum (for Primary &amp; Secondary students);</li>\n	<li>Identify important protocols and practices in the effective use of blogs including privacy and communication with parents/guardians;</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><u>Here is some feedback we have had from teachers about this Workshop:</u></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>“EDU-mazing!! Perfect course for 21st century learners.” – Felicity.</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>“Totally worth it! I have left with 2 blogs created &amp; a heap of resources to go &amp; explore &amp; play with.” – Jessica.</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>“A great day, a lot of interesting, exciting and engaging information was given. It really gave me a new enthusiasm for blogging within my classroom. A great tool to get the kids excited.” – Kate.</em></p>', 'The Power of Blogging- Burwood', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'the-power-of-blogging-burwood', '', '', '2015-11-07 03:55:05', '2015-11-07 03:55:05', '', 0, 'http://teachmepd.com.au/', 0, 'tribe_events', '', 0),
(574, 18, '2015-11-07 03:55:05', '2015-11-07 03:55:05', '<p style="text-align: center;"><em><strong>Are you a Graduate, Preservice Teacher, CRT, or Returning teacher planning to transition into a primary classroom?</strong></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><strong>Do you wish you knew easy and innovative ways to enhance your teaching and student learning?</strong></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><strong> If you answered yes, than this Innovation Meet is for you.</strong></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Get <strong>READY </strong>for a full day of professional learning experiences that will <strong>SET </strong>you up for teaching success and support you to <strong>LEARN </strong>how to have an edumazing year within a <strong>primary school</strong><span class="apple-converted-space">.</span></p>\r\n<strong>Suitability:</strong>\r\n\r\nThis Innovation Meet is for educators in the primary school sector, in particular: Graduates, Preservice Teachers, CRTs, and Returning teachers transitioning into a primary school classroom.\r\n\r\n<strong>The <em>Behaviour</em>torium</strong>\r\n\r\nDiscover practical strategies to support you to work more effectively with challenging behaviours. Understand the language of behaviour, and how it links to children’s thoughts, feelings and needs. Experience a holistic behaviour framework that increases understanding of the child and simple steps you can take to minimise harm and maximise learning. Uncover simple ways you can foster connection and learning to increase positive behaviours in the classroom and engage all students to thrive.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>The <em>Empowerment</em> Zone</strong>\r\n\r\nStep up and empower yourself as a teacher moving from the ordinary to the extraordinary.  Develop a powerful teacher blueprint as an activator of learning, and set achievable expectations.  Learn how a growth mindset will allow you and your students to create a learning culture that fosters student personalised and self-directed learning where all students achieve ongoing success. This includes using practical assessment strategies, planning techniques and digital tools to drive powerful progressive learning and pedagogy. Extend your communication skills and improve relationships with your students, colleagues and parents.  Learn how to nurture habits that will keep you organised, focused and passionate about each working day.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>The <em>Maker</em>Pit</strong>\r\n\r\n<span class="apple-converted-space">Experience a combined</span> innovative maker-space and hands-on learning sandpit to improve learning from the onset. Join us and be inspired to explore, make and discover learning experiences that will engage and stimulate your students socially, physically, intellectually, culturally and emotionally. Grow your classroom and young minds with limitless engaging possibilities that shape deeper learning across the curriculum.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Three more ways to supercharge your learning:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe <em><strong>Connect</strong></em><strong>ion Hub </strong>is a private collaborative online space where you will all be excited to share ideas, explore challenges, solve problems and support one another to continually grow and improve your teaching from this point forward. It is your very own Professional Learning Network that brings together professionals with common interests and needs.\r\n\r\nThe <em><strong>Playground </strong></em>is our common meeting place during recess and lunchtime. Enjoy the playground puzzlers that will engage and disrupt you, while you dine, talk and laugh with other educational innovators.  It’s the perfect place to reimagine learning and to share great ideas.\r\n\r\nAfterwards, let’s meet up at the <em><strong>Happiness Hangout </strong></em>for mindset-making, dream-catching, challenge-busting and celebrating your new professional journey to come.\r\n\r\n<strong>Innovation Meet Registration and Cost:</strong>\r\n\r\nRegistration for Ready…Set…Learn is made online, and allows for individual and group bookings.  Be sure to take advantage of our special prices:\r\n\r\nIf you register now (by Sunday 15<sup>th </sup>of November 2015), you will receive the promotion price of $175 inc GST.\r\n\r\nIf you register by Sunday 27<sup>th</sup>of December 2015, you will receive the early bird price of $199 inc GST.\r\n\r\nIf you register from Monday 28<sup>th</sup>December 2015, you will receive our last minute price of $220 inc GST\r\n\r\n<strong>*N.B. There are no withdrawals or cancellations for this event.</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Innovation Meet: Ready...Set...Learn! - Preston', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'innovation-meet-ready-set-learn-preston', '', '', '2015-11-18 06:08:45', '2015-11-18 06:08:45', '', 0, 'http://teachmepd.com.au/', 0, 'tribe_events', '', 0),
